WUTHERING HEIGHTS.

CHAPTER I.

ANOTHER week over--and I am so many days
nearer health, and spring! I have now heard
all my neighbour's history, at different sittings,
as the housekeeper could spare time from more
important occupations. I'll continue it in her
own words, only a little condensed. She is,
on the whole, a very fair narrator and I don't
think I could improve her style.
